<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-475-559  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 475 559.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  Oct 1990 v16 n10p1136(14).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A visual language compiler for information retrieval by visualreasoning. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chang, Shi-Kuo.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Retrieving information is a major problem for users of very largedata bases.andP;  One method is to use visual reasoning, which is theprocess of reasoning and making inferences based upon visuallypresented clues.andP;  A visual language compiler can transform thedata objects and present sample data objects in a visual space.andO;The prototype system, which is implemented in C, has four mainfeatures: it is built on top of the visual language compiler,enabling it to be customized; it supports a fuzzy icon grammar; itincorporates a semantic model of the data base for fuzzy visualquery translation; and it has a VisualNet where the knowledge thesystem learns is stored.andP;  The prototype system can use what itlearns to adapt its behavior.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Visual ProgrammingResearch and DevelopmentC Programming LanguageCompilersInformation Storage and RetrievalData Bases.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The visual space. (chart)Zoom-in to a smaller region. (chart)Zoom-out to a larger space. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>